sentences: Denny Seiwell (born July 10, 1943) is an American drummer and a founding member of Paul McCartney and Wings.
He is a graduate of Lehighton High School and was a member of the first Carbon County Band in 1961.
After leaving the band, Seiwell eventually moved to Los Angeles, where he has resided since 1975.
Seiwell stated in 2019 that he and McCartney have kept in touch since 1993.

In 2021, Seiwell produced Ram On - The 50th Anniversary Tribute to Paul and Linda McCartney's Ram with Fernando Perdomo.

His drumming was used in TV shows such as Happy Days and Knots Landing.
